00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:21.071
For the American viewers of Aha Yemi Ruchi, Mrs. Sailaja from 
Madison, Alabama has welcomed us to her home

00:00:30.628 --> 00:00:34.556
What are you going to cook for us?
I'll be making Vada

00:00:35.385 --> 00:00:37.764
Ingredients required to make Vada

00:00:38.018 --> 00:00:44.360
Green Gram, Black Gram, Red Gram, Bengal Gram, Pepper, Coriander Seeds

00:00:44.718 --> 00:00:47.318
Cumin Seeds, Mustard Seeds &amp; Oil

00:00:48.377 --> 00:01:02.989
Firstly, soak the green, red, black and bengal gram in water for 5 hours.
One cup each will do.

00:01:06.950 --> 00:01:17.559
Now, grind all the four soaked grams into a coarse powder

00:01:20.614 --> 00:01:36.987
Also, grind 10 dry red chillies, 1 tbsp of pepper, coriander seeds
 &amp; cumin seeds and 1 tsp of mustard seeds into a powder

00:01:38.164 --> 00:01:45.364
Now, add the spices powder and salt to the ground gram powder
 and mix with water to get a moist texture and consistency

00:01:55.694 --> 00:02:04.975
Take a pan and heat some oil for deep frying

00:02:47.714 --> 00:03:04.137
Roll the mixture into small patties and deep fry them

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:49.299
Once they're fried to a golden tinge, take them in a serving plate

